    <p>On Nov 15, 1943, El­iz­a­beth Choy Su-Moi was ar­rested for her sus­pected in­volve­ment in the anti-Ja­panese op­er­a­tion</p>
    <p>Jay­wick. Over the next 200 days, she faced bru­tal in­ter­ro­ga­tions that in­cluded phys­i­cal and psy­cho­log­i­cal tor­ture. The creators of Lieu­tenant Ad­nan And The Last Reg­i­ment (2017), Danny Jalil and Zaki Rag­man, are back with a graphic novel about the war hero­ine. In this vir­tual launch by Asi­a­pac Books, the creators and other guest speak­ers re­flect on Choy’s legacy.</p>
    <p>WHERE: str.sg/J8J7</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row, 3pm</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free</p>


